Probabilistic Methods. 

Explanation: The paper focuses on the Expectation-Maximization (EM) algorithm, which is a probabilistic method used for maximum-likelihood parameter estimation. The paper also discusses the application of the EM algorithm to two specific probabilistic models: mixture of Gaussian densities and hidden Markov models. The paper does not discuss any other sub-categories of AI such as Case Based, Genetic Algorithms, Neural Networks, Reinforcement Learning, Rule Learning, or Theory.
